*   **Count & Layers:** The structure uses 19 blocks and has 5 layers.
*   **Spatial Relationships:**

    *   Layer 2: A horizontal yellow block (index 6) sits above the right-most block with arch (index 1). A yellow block (index 9) and a green block (index 8) are placed to the left of the center arch block (index 2). There is also a red block with a curved face and an arc shape underneath (index 3) sits under a green block (index 8).
    *   Layer 3: A green block (index 7) is stacked directly above the green block (index 8) and a yellow rectangular block (index 10) is on top of the green block (index 6). There is also a green block (index 7) on top of the curved red block (index 3).
    *   Layer 4: Two blue cube blocks (index 4) are stacked on the green rectangular blocks (index 7), a yellow rectangular block (index 10) on top of the yellow rectangular block (index 10).
    *   Layer 5: A rectangular orange block (index 15) is on top of the orange block (index 16).
